  "prompt": "Who are some celebrity users of Quora?",
  "response": "Quora has attracted a diverse range of users, including celebrities from various fields. Here are a few notable celebrities who have been active on the platform:\n\n1. **Will Wheaton** - Known for his roles in *Star Trek: The Next Generation* and *The Big Bang Theory*, Wheaton has been an active Quora user, sharing insights on acting, writing, and geek culture.\n\n2. **Dustin Moskovitz** - Co-founder of Facebook and Asana, Moskovitz has used Quora to share his thoughts on entrepreneurship, technology, and philanthropy.\n\n3. **Ashton Kutcher** - The actor and investor has answered questions on Quora about startups, acting, and his personal life.\n\n4. **Naval Ravikant** - Co-founder of AngelList, Ravikant is a frequent Quora contributor, offering advice on entrepreneurship, investing, and life philosophy.\n\n5. **Steve Huffman** - Co-founder of Reddit, Huffman has answered questions about the tech industry, startups, and his experiences in Silicon Valley.\n\nThese celebrities often share valuable insights and personal experiences, making Quora a unique platform for learning from well-known figures across different industries. It\u2019s worth noting that some celebrities may use pseudonyms or may not be consistently active, but their contributions have left a lasting impact on the platform.",
